<subsection xml:id="subsec-representation-of-data">
    <title>Representation of Data</title>
    <introduction xml:id="auto_ku9jyvb7">
        <p xml:id="auto_4344phmm">
            Representation of data is the process of presenting collected information (data) in an organized and visual form so that it is easy to understand, interpret and analyze.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_rhwovzn8">
            Instead of leaving data as raw numbers, we use tables, charts and graphs to show patterns, trends, and comparisons more clearly.
        </p>
    </introduction>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-drawing-histograms-and-frequency-polygons-of-data">
        <title>Drawing Histograms and Frequency Polygons of Data</title>
